The paper focuses on biomedical image segmentation using deep neural networks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a design to exploit the computation power of blockchain, which falls under cryptography and security (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses digital signatures and network overhead, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
